<P>
   &UR; ALBRIGHT IS HAVEL'S HANDPICKED SUCCESSOR, RUMOR CLAIMS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (UNDATED) _ U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright arrives
in Prague next week on a trip that many in her native capital see
as a declaration of interest in the country's presidency.
Czech-born Albright is being touted as a possible replacement for
Vaclav Havel, whose term of office ends in 2002. Havel told
Albright a year and a half ago that he wanted her to replace him,
according to a report in Time magazine Monday. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By Adam Lebor, The Independent of London &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Moved Mon., Feb. 28) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (525 words) &QL;
