<P>
   TV-COPBEAT _ Imagine a police force in which recruits must study
child development, where ranking officers can study clinical
psychology at Yale, and where any officer must surrender his pager
number to any citizen who requests it. They're doing that in New
Haven, Conn., where a 10-year ``experiment'' in community policing
is still underway. ``New Cop on the Beat'' a one-hour PBS
documentary airing Wednesday night at 10, shows a little about what
New Haven is doing, but skimps on some key information. (Grieco,
Dayton Daily News). 15.
