<P>
   GARDENING-LIFE _ A gardening column by Lee May. This week: As
March ushers houseplants off center stage, let us give thanks to
our tireless potted friends that labored mightily throughout the
winter to keep our homes agrowth. My interior plants number far
fewer than several years ago. This big changes have come come
through giveaways, throwaways and deaths. Like paring down anyplace
_ in the outdoor garden or in life _ the slimmer indoor collection
offers increased opportunities to appreciate what remains.(May,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
