imminently affordable wine. By MICHAEL LONSFORD (For release
Friday, March 3).
</P>
<P>
   PILLSBURY-BAKEOFF (San Francisco) _ It was a great celebration
of suburbia in the midst of this ever-so-hip, cosmopolitan city.
San Francisco, the home of restaurants founded by Jeremiah Tower
and Wolfgang Puck, played host Monday to a group of less-famous
chefs: 99 amateur cooks from across the country who competed in the
50th anniversary Pillsbury Bake-Off cooking contest. By EMILY
GURNON.
</P>
