religion, reform and who's the real Reagan Republican, John McCain
and George W. Bush are blowing off Ronald Reagan's home state. By
ROB MORSE.
</P>
<P>
   SALTER-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ I don't know what the California
version is of the Congressional Medal of Honor, but I think State
Sen. Debra Bowen ought to get one. A Democrat, Bowen has finally
done something so sensible _ and overdue _ it's hard to believe it
came from a politician. She introduced a bill that would require
the California Public Utilities Commission to assign new telephone
area codes on the basis of technology, not geography. By STEPHANIE
SALTER.
</P>
