<P>
   &UR; HAIDER GOOSE-STEPS DOWN AMID DER FUROR &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BERLIN _ The Austrian far-right leader Joerg Haider stunned
political friends and foes alike by announcing Monday that he
wanted to step down as leader of the Freedom Party. But there is no
danger of Haider, the most successful politician in postwar Austria
and an ambitious chancellor wannabe, disappearing from the scene.
In fact, his retreat is likely to prove a tactical gambit. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Commentary Editors) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By Imre Karacs, The Independent of London &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Moved Mon., Feb. 28) &QL;
