<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; COMMENTARY &LR;  &QC;  &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; A FUNNY THING HAPPENED ON THE WAY TO THE CORONATION... &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   This week the Republican Party took one great step forward and
one huge step back in its quest to recapture the White House. The
Republican race between John McCain and George W. Bush, now heading
towards a showdown in New York and California on March 7, is the
most exciting one since Gerald Ford and Ronald Reagan duked it out
in 1976. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Commentary Editors) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (900 words) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Moved as BC-GOP-HUMDINGER!-ECONOMIST-NYTSF &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; A GODSEND FOR THE GREAT SATAN. SEIZE IT, AMERICA &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``An event of historic proportions,'' was the Clinton
administration's judgment on the reformists' victory in Iran's
parliamentary election last weekend. Can the United States now
build on this historic, but still fragile, event by improving its
own sour relations with the Islamic republic? The election offers
the U.S. a ripe opportunity to help the reformists and further its
own strategic interests. Don't squander it, America. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Commentary Editors) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (700 words) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Moved as BC-IRAN-US-DEFROST-ECONOMIST-NYTSF &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHY BUSINESS IS DOTTY ABOUT DOT.COMMERCE &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The Internet is profoundly affecting almost all business and
commerce. Is it a fleeting fancy, or a life-changing love? That
question lingers over today's obsession with the Internet. Let's
sift through the sense and nonsense surrounding the
business-to-consumer e-commerce boom... &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Commentary Editors) &QL;
</P>
