</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-HAVASU (Undated) _ In the land of the Havasupai _ The
People of the Blue-green Water -- water is always on one's mind. It
weighs down packs. Hikers drink more than you would imagine if you
had not hiked in the arid Southwest. By John Cunningham. (2 takes)
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-SANTA-MONICA (Santa Monica, Calif.) _ You can't help
liking a town that may be an affluent celebrity haven but whose
signature structure is a humble Ferris wheel. By William A. Davis.
1540 words.
</P>
<P>
