   CULTURE
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``e'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   THEATER-NAMES (New York) _ Broadway's historic legitimate
theaters have been named for actors and actresses, playwrights and
critics, theater owners and patrons of the arts. Not until today
have any of them been named for airline companies. But in an
$8.5-million dollar deal that may well foreshadow the corporate
renaming of a host of Broadway houses, a nonprofit theater group is
rechristening the venerable Selwyn Theater on 42nd Street the
``American Airlines Theater.'' Meanwhile, the Winter Garden
Theater, where ``Cats'' is due to close in June after an 18-year
run, may soon become the Cadillac Theater or the Cadillac Winter
Garden. By Ralph Blumenthal and Robin Pogrebin.
</P>
<P>
   With graphic.
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``a'' news file.)
