<P>
   NY-HOSP-FINE (New York) _ In one of its harshest actions against
a New York City hospital in over a decade, the state Department of
Health on Tuesday cited Staten Island University Hospital for 40
violations and fined the hospital $80,000 for failing to monitor
and discipline its chief of neurosurgery, who the state said, among
other things, operated on the wrong side of a patient's brain, for
the second time in five years. By Jennifer Steinhauer.
</P>
<P>
   NY-DIALLO (New York) _ Federal prosecutors will likely have
difficulty bringing civil rights charges against the four New York
City police officers who were acquitted in the death of Amadou
Diallo, legal experts say, but they will be working under Justice
Department guidelines written broadly enough to allow them to file
a case if they want to. By Jane Fritsch.
</P>
