r l BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRO     02-29 0752
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 Copyright 2000 Chronicle Publishing Company 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SCALIA CONTEMPLATES CHANGING JOBS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Supreme Court Justice  &UR; Antonin Scalia &LR; 's been depressed, says
Washingtonian magazine, because he can't seem to get his fellow
justices to allow states to set abortion rules. Conservatives
 &UR; William Rehnquist &LR;  and  &UR; Anthony Kennedy &LR;  have been disappointments
to Scalia; only  &UR; Clarence Thomas &LR;  is a proven ally.
</P>
<P>
   According to the magazine, Scalia is waiting for the outcome of
the presidential election to decide on his future.
</P>
<P>
   If a Democrat wins, he's unlikely to ever been &LR;  made chief
justice, and he will probably resign. If a Republican wins, there's
a chance that Scalia or Thomas will be appointed chief justice when
Rehnquist retires. Scalia will stay on, hoping that happens.
</P>
<P>
   The magazine notes, too, that the New York law firm Davis Polk &AMP;
Wardwell is paying first-year associates right out of law school
$150,000 to $160,000 a year. Scalia's salary on the court is only
$167,900 a year, another motivation for him to change jobs.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ON THE WAY TO THE PRESIDENCY &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Questioned by the Republican pollster  &UR; Frank Luntz &LR; , whose
survey is reported on the political Web site YROCK.com _ YROCK is
Young Republican Online Community Network _ GOP women named
 &UR; George W. Bush &LR;  the best prospective spouse among the presidential
hopefuls, men picked him as the best best man and people of both
genders were in agreement that he was most likely to have cheated
in college.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; John McCain &LR;  got top ranking as preferred father and landlord,
and babysitter for a 16-year-old daughter.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Al Gore &LR;  was selected as preferred lifeline for voters if they
were to appear on ``Who Wants to Be a Millionaire.'' He was also
chosen as probably the worst to listen to at a karaoke bar.
</P>
<P>
   P.S.  &UR; Joe Shea &LR;  of the American Reporter says McCain was seen
chewing ice while making chitchat with supporters at a Los Angeles
fund-raiser. And  &UR; Bill Bradley &LR; 's campaign has issued a press
release saying the candidate was holding a series of ``visibilities
at key locations'' in Maryland Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MOO AND BOO &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Inspired by the National Milk Producers Federation's campaign to
banish the term ``soy milk,''  &UR; Michael Babcock &LR;  stirs up some other
cauldrons:
</P>
<P>
   ``How about jelly beans?'' he writes. ``Just the other day, I
bought a batch to make some chile con carne, and you can believe it
turned out lousy! Why, it's neither jelly nor bean.'' Furthermore,
he asks, ``Ever tried to drink baking soda?''
</P>
<P>
   Similarly, travel writer  &UR; Carole Terwilliger Meyers &LR;  wonders why
the group isn't complaining about coconut milk. ``Is that because
they think it lactates from breasts, because women have been
observed wearing coconut shells over same?''
</P>
<P>
   Meyers, a woman with the tropics on her mind, will be part of a
``Travelers' Tales Hawaii'' reading tonight at Get Lost Travel in
San Francisco.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   - At a premiere party in New York for the movie ``Judy Berlin,''
director  &UR; Whit Stillman &LR;  told Personals spy  &UR; Baird Jones &LR;  that he's
just finished writing a script, with  &UR; George Plimpton &LR; , ``about the
early days of the Paris Review when  &UR; Jane Fonda &LR;  and all these
college girls came over to Paris to help start up the literary
magazine.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; - Linda Denizard &LR; , chef at a Miami restaurant owned by  &UR; Ricky &LR; 
 &UR; Martin &LR; , is trying to find a publisher for a Ricky Martin cookbook,
which will include her recipes and his introduction. The New York
Daily News says this is expected to get an advance in the (large)
$500,000-to-$1 million range.
</P>
<P>
   - Conceptual artist  &UR; Lawrence Weiner &LR;  has two Manhattan
installations _ including one at the Dia Art Foundation Center _ in
which he has relabeled the men's and ladies' rooms, &LR;  Us and Them.
Because the Dia Foundation is incorporated as a nonprofit group,
some picky art lovers are wondering if the labels are
discriminatory.
</P>
<P>
   - One of the third-place winners in the Good Vibrations
Millennium Sex Toys contest is a device activated by pager (not to
be more fully described in a family newspaper).
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``We believe she can be a Martha Stewart for girls.''
</P>
<P>
   -  &UR; Adrienne Fontanella &LR; , president of the Barbie division of
Mattel, telling the Wall Street Journal that she hopes a new Barbie
_ with belly button, bigger hips and  &LR; a  &LR; smaller bust -will help
sell all kinds of products.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
