<P>
   BUSH-McCAIN (Washington) _ Sen. John McCain faces increasingly
tough races in crucial presidential primaries in California and New
York on March 7, in part because Roman Catholic voters are
responding to Texas Gov. George W. Bush's apology for failing to
criticize anti-Catholic teachings at Bob Jones University. John
Zogby, a Utica, N.Y.-based pollster who is not affiliated with
either candidate, says that McCain's narrow lead over Bush is now
vulnerable because of movement toward Bush by Roman Catholic
voters. By STEWART M. POWELL and DAN FREEDMAN. (Already filed.)
