u s BC-HKN-MCSORLEY-BOS &LR;      02-29 0327
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HKN-MCSORLEY-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
POLICE TO REPORT ON MCSORLEY-BRASHEAR ASSAULT 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By KEVIN PAUL DUPONT  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Vancouver Police Department is nearing the end of its
investigation into last week's Marty McSorley-Donald Brashear
assault and could forward its findings to the Crown Prosecutor's
office in British Columbia as early as Wednesday, a police
department spokesperson said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Anne Drennan, constable for the Vancouver PD, said the
investigative team of three, including a sergeant/overseer and two
department investigators, should have the case file on the Crown
Prosecutor's desk by no later than Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
   ``In this Province, the police department does not lay
charges,'' said Drennan, who said the department was unwilling to
share with the media the scope of the investigation, including how
many people would be interviewed by the investigators. ``All the
information will be forwarded to the Crown Prosecutor _ the
equivalent of the District Attorney in the States _ and that office
will decide if charges are to be layed.''
</P>
<P>
   Drennan confirmed the charge being investigated is assault,
specifically assault with a weapon (i.e. a hockey stick).
</P>
<P>
   McSorley clubbed Brashear to the ice with 2.7 seconds remaining
in the Bruins' 5-2 loss to the Canucks last Monday night at General
Motors Place. The rugged Brashear, who appeared to be knocked cold
on his feet when McSorley struck him over the right temple with his
stick, is recovering from a severe (Grade 3) concussion and likely
won't return before April 9, the conclusion of the NHL's regular
season.
</P>
<P>
   McSorley, unavailable to the media since his initial comments
after the incident, last week was suspended through the conclusion
of the 1999-2000 season, including the playoffs. He is not expected
to comment again before the Crown Prosector determines whether to
push forward with charges.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-02-29-00 2020EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
