<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-29 21:14 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2528 &Cx1f; tad-z
u a BC-LEWIS-AUTOPSY01-COX     02-29 0724
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEWIS-AUTOPSY01-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Autopsy report: Crowd attacked Atlanta slaying victims
 &HT;    By Lyda Longa
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Two men stabbed to death in a melee hours after the
Super Bowl were attacked by as many as 10 people, according to
autopsy reports released Tuesday by the Fulton County Medical
Examiner's Office.
</P>
<P>
   One of the slain men sustained a 4-inch-long cut across his
abdomen, the autopsy found.
</P>
<P>
   The reports, which describe how Jacinth Baker and Richard Lollar
died at an Atlanta intersection, also indicates the two Decatur,
Ga., men may have been stabbed with two different knives.
</P>
<P>
   Lollar's wounds show he was stabbed with a knife that has a
serrated edge, while Baker's wounds showed no evidence of
serration, said Dr. John Parker, an assistant Fulton County medical
examiner.
</P>
<P>
   ``That could mean they were stabbed with different knives or the
identical knives were used but the angle may have been different,''
said Parker, who performed the autopsies.
</P>
<P>
   The reports, obtained Tuesday by The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution, show Lollar was stabbed and sliced four times
and died of a 3- or 3 1/2-inch-deep wound to the heart. Baker was
stabbed three times and died of a 3-inch-deep wound that penetrated
the heart. A 4-inch-long, 3-inch-deep abdominal cut penetrated his
liver.
</P>
<P>
   Baker also suffered bruises to his face, forehead and nose.
Parker said that was consistent with falling on the pavement after
he was attacked.
</P>
<P>
   Baltimore Ravens football star Ray Lewis, Reginald Oakley and
Joseph Sweeting have all been indicted on murder charges. Lewis is
out of jail on bail and is under a court-supervised curfew in
Maryland; the other two are jailed in Atlanta awaiting trial.
</P>
<P>
   Neither District Attorney Paul Howard nor Atlanta police would
say Tuesday whether they were seeking more arrests in the case,
citing a gag order.
</P>
<P>
   Medical examiner's investigators, who arrived at the scene
shortly after police, interviewed witnesses and prepared a report
on each victim that is attached as part of the medical examiner's
autopsy report.
</P>
<P>
   Investigator Teresa R. Price said witnesses told her that ``10
men jumped on the two men and stabbed and shot at'' Lollard and
Baker, her report shows.
</P>
<P>
   No one has since alleged that shots were fired at Baker and
Lollar, although shots reportedly were fired at the limousine after
the altercation.
</P>
<P>
   Price's report that more than three people fought with Lollar
and Baker is consistent with what cabdriver Patrick I. Ozonu, a
witness to part of the incident, told the Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   ``What I saw was six guys beating up a guy, right at the
intersection,'' Ozonu said. ``There was a commotion. Six people
were beating up one guy _ but there was a commotion. That means it
could have been more people, more than six.''
</P>
<P>
   And only a few hours after the killings, Lollar's fiancee,
Kellye Smith, told the Journal-Constitution, an undercover Atlanta
police investigator who had been working near the fight scene told
her he had seen 10 people fighting with Baker and Lollar.
</P>
<P>
   ``He told me he yelled out, `There's 10 on two,''' Smith said.
``He said he thought of trying to get into the fight to help, but
then thought better of it because there were so many people.''
</P>
<P>
   Two weeks ago, Atlanta police investigators and one of Lewis'
attorneys, Ed Garland, said at least 12 people had been riding in
the Lincoln Navigator stretch limousine Lewis rented to party in
Atlanta during the Super Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   The passengers included Lewis, driver Duane Fassett, Oakley,
Sweeting and two women.
</P>
<P>
   At Lewis' bond hearing, police Investigator Ken Allen said
Sweeting and Lewis went to the Sports Authority in Duluth, Ga.,
during the weekend and Sweeting purchased three knives.
</P>
<P>
   Police have said that at least one of the knives Sweeting
purchased was a small folding knife that attaches to the index
finger. The only knife fitting that description at the Sports
Authority is the Gerber Chameleon II. The knife is partially
serrated.
</P>
<P>
   The plastic package that holds the $20 knife is emblazoned with
the words ``For all your adventures'' on the front.
</P>
<P>
   Atlanta Journal-Constitution staff writer Mike Fish contributed
to this article.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
