<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; STARTOVER _ &LR;  After a dozen years as an investment banker helping
entrepreneurs launch their businesses, Abby Adlerman decided it was
time to start her own enterprise.
</P>
<P>
   In mid-1998, she created Visualize.com to sell limited-edition
original prints and photographs to fill the void between expensive
gallery pieces and mass-produced posters. ``I went from Wall Street
to wall art,'' she said. Adlerman is not alone. Hundreds of
investment bankers, venture capitalists and securities analysts
have plunged into building their own enterprises or taking top jobs
with those who have. By Peter Sinton
</P>
