<P>
   BC-VOTER-TURNOUT-NYT (moved on Friday, Feb. 25)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, Feb. 25,
incorrectly to a record for a Michigan's Republican primary. While
more people voted this time than in the 1976 primary, this year's
turnout was not a record. Because the voting-age population has
grown, the turnout was 17 percent of those eligible, compared with
the record of 17.4 in 1976.
</P>
